   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Heras (?), son of Heras, whose mother is Thaesis (?), daughter of Horos, from the city of Oxyrhynchos, Persian of the epigone,  to Paas . . . , son of Horos, whose mother is Sinthonis, [l. 5] from the same city, greetings.  I too have received from you from hand to hand, out of the house, 100 drachmas of imperial silver coinage, total 100 drachmas, and to have had measured to me 2 artabas of wheat, out of the house, total 2 artabas, as a capital sum [l. 10] to which nothing at all has been added, which I will return in the month of Pauni of the current third year of the Emperor Caesar Nerva Trajan Augustus Germanicus . . .</ab>
         </div>
